  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C).",
    "In a large skillet, sauté diced onion and carrot in a splash of oat milk until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add minced garlic, thyme, bay leaf, cinnamon stick, turmeric, salt, and pepper, and stir for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in pearl barley and vegetable broth, bring to a simmer, then cover and cook for 25 minutes until barley is tender.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a greased baking dish, pour oat milk over the top, and bake uncovered for 15 minutes.",
    "Remove the dish, lift the cinnamon stick, and allow the casserole to cool and set for 5 minutes.",
    "Serve the casserole warm, optionally garnished with fresh herbs.",
    "Enjoy the comforting, anti-inflammatory flavors of this Norwegian-inspired one-pot dish."
  ],
